Detection Scans

--> Service Version Detection
nmap -sV <target>
Identifies what software and version is running on open ports.
Use when: You need to know the exact software behind a service.

--> OS Detection
nmap -O <target>
Tries to identify the operating system.
Use when: You want to know if a device runs Linux, Windows, etc. Needs root/sudo.

--> Aggressive Scan
nmap -A <target>
Does everything â€” OS detection, version detection, scripts, and traceroute.
Use when: You want full information about a target. Loud and noticeable.
